  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Exit grant-Building Community Resilience to Climate Change - Second tranche</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">-Enhancing  livelihood diversification support in the island of Tubigon in Bohol, but with particular focus on vulnerable groups such as the elderly, particularly women as we aim to demonstrate elderly&#x2019; and women&#x2019;s aspirations to productive aging, financial security as we introduce elderly and water-friendly farming livelihood opportunities while enhancing community support groups to ensure their need for connectedness.
-Testing of the EN Decision Guide in partnership with Bohol Provincial Government. Bohol remains one of the most vulnerable to drought particularly after the 2013 earthquake. Through this protocol for EN Response, we hope to improve their preparedness to drought and investments in water conservation and management.  
-Support small community water projects in support to their livelihood diversification p
-Enhance Tubigon&#x2019;s climate services for agriculture.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is being proposed to further push innovations in R1&#x2019;s work on climate resilience both at the community level and in terms of capacitating local governments in the context of small islands. It will also build on the latest work of R1 in the area of El Nino preparedness and in our PSF accession victory in Tarlac.</narrative>
  </description>
